\newlabel{fig:per_foundation}{{6}{8}{Per-foundation $\Delta R$ (top row) and $\Delta S$ (bottom row), Eq.~\eqref {eq:delta}, for insecure (left column) and secure (right column) variants. Error bars denote propagated standard errors. Insecure fine-tuning produces a more uniform robustness collapse and suceptibility spike across foundations; secure fine-tuning produces more uneven, foundation-specific shifts}{figure.6}{}}
